"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453606","Department for Transport","false","2016-03-03","<p>The filters are changed in accordance with the manufacturer's routine maintenance schedules. It is in the operator's interest to change the filters in accordance with the schedule; with time the pores in the filters become congested with material.</p><p> </p><p>This congestion can increase the efficiency of the filter in removing particles from the air, but also increases the resistance to air flow. Therefore greater pressure and power is required to maintain the cabin air flow, which in turn increases fuel-burn and therefore costs.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-03-03T12:34:46.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453606/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453606/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453606/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-22","Aircraft: Air Conditioning","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what are the requirements on airlines using UK airports for frequently changing air filters in all cabins and what is the maximum permitted interval between changing air filters.","false","Biography information for Lord Freeman",,"Lord Freeman","HL6308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453607","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-03","<p>The Government established the Freedom of Information Commission to review the Freedom of Information Act and we will give careful consideration to its recommendations. Section 8(1)(b) of the FOI Act already requires applicants to provide their real name.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2016-03-03T14:54:11.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453607/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453607/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453607/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-22","Freedom of Information","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to make any changes to freedom of information legislation, in particular on the use of false names when seeking disclosure; and if so, what changes they propose, and when will they be brought forward.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL6309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453608","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-03-01","<p>I am informed that the authorities in the Republic of Ireland have not banned all Church of Ireland services in the centre of Dublin on Easter Sunday but that there will be restricted access to the city centre on that day due to security measures being put it place around a planned Easter Rising Commemoration parade.</p><p> </p><p>I understand that the Irish Government and An Garda Síochána are working closely with senior Church of Ireland representatives in order to facilitate worship at those churches in the area. This matter has not been raised under the human rights arrangements within the Belfast Agreement 1998.</p>",,"Lord Dunlop",,"2016-03-01T15:44:44.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453608/answer","Biography information for Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453608/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453608/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-02-22","Church Services: Republic of Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether under the human rights arrangements within the Belfast Agreement 1998, they have raised or will raise the decision by the authorities in the Republic of Ireland to ban all Church of Ireland services in the centre of Dublin on Easter Sunday, and if they have raised this matter, what was the result.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL6310"
