"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453693","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-29","<p>While ticket prices are matter for individual clubs, this Government is aware how important this is to so many football fans. Football is enjoying an enormous amount of financial success at present, however it should not be forgotten that this is built on the hard work and the money of millions of loyal supporters. Clubs should ensure that ticket pricing strikes the right balance between value for supporters, and generating the income necessary to sustain their business.</p><p> </p><p>I will be looking for football to embrace fully a key recommendation from a recently published Government Expert Working Group on supporter ownership and engagement that requires clubs meet with fans at least twice yearly to discuss matters of most importance.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","27783","2016-02-29T15:21:13.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453693/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453693/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453693/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-22","Football: Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he plans to take to help prevent disproportionate increases in the price of football tickets.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","27674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453694","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-25","<p>My officials and staff in the Gambling Commission meet a range of stakeholders and representative bodies at regular intervals to discuss gambling policy and regulation. Information on Ministers' meetings with external organisations are included in the quarterly transparency returns.</p><p> </p><p>The Government published its evaluation of the £50 regulations introduced in April 2015 on 21 January. The evaluation paper can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-of-gaming-machine-circumstances-of-useamendment-regulations-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-of-gaming-machine-circumstances-of-useamendment-regulations-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>We will now consider the findings of the evaluation before deciding if there is a need for further action.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","27597","2016-02-25T11:53:50.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453694/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453694/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453694/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-22","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what representative bodies (a) his Department and (b) the Gambling Commission has met to discuss the next review of gaming machines stakes and prizes.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","27596"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453695","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-25","<p>My officials and staff in the Gambling Commission meet a range of stakeholders and representative bodies at regular intervals to discuss gambling policy and regulation. Information on Ministers' meetings with external organisations are included in the quarterly transparency returns.</p><p> </p><p>The Government published its evaluation of the £50 regulations introduced in April 2015 on 21 January. The evaluation paper can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-of-gaming-machine-circumstances-of-useamendment-regulations-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-of-gaming-machine-circumstances-of-useamendment-regulations-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>We will now consider the findings of the evaluation before deciding if there is a need for further action.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","27596","2016-02-25T11:53:51.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453695/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453695/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453695/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-22","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when his Department plans to launch the next triennial review of gaming machine stake and prize limits.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","27597"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453696","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-01","<p>The statutory target for audio description is 10% for most broadcasters. The BBC in 2010 committed a higher target and now provides audio description of 20% of its content on BBC One, BBC Two, BBC Three, BBC Four, CBBC and CBeebies.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-03-01T12:35:21.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453696/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453696/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453696/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-22","BBC","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will make representations to the BBC on increasing the provision of voice-overs for BBC programmes.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","27600"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453697","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-25","<p>The Ministry of Defence has regular discussions with the US Government and F-35 industry partners about the F-35 Lightning II programme, including the Autonomic Logistics Information System (ALIS). The ALIS has been subject to a comprehensive programme of testing and risk assessment. It has been designed to be resilient against cyber-attack and will continue to be the subject of testing throughout the life of the programme.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-02-25T16:03:17.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453697/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453697/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453697/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-22","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions his Department has had on the F-35's digital logistics system and its potential vulnerability to cyber attacks.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","27678"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453698","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-29","<p>Defence Exercises such as Joint Venture 16 require the assistance of Partners Across Government to replicate the interoperability and inputs which a deployed Joint Task Force would face on operations. The following Government Departments and agencies have been invited to participate in Exercise Joint Venture: the Ministry of Defence, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office, the Department for International Development, the Stabilisation Unit, Dstl and various Intelligence Agencies.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-29T16:58:04.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453698/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453698/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453698/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-22","Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which government departments and agencies plan to participate in Exercise Joint Venture later this year.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","27661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453699","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my right hon. Friend the Cabinet Office Minister (Matthew Hancock) to her Question 27634 on 26 February 2016.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-03-01T16:38:10.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453699/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453699/answer","20160226_27634_Meetings.docx","20160226_27634_Meetings.docx","QnA extract on Meetings","QnA extract on Meetings","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453699/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-22","Ministry of Defence: Meetings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what meetings (a) he and (b) Ministers of his Department have had with (i) arms manufacturers, (ii) tobacco manufacturers and (iii) representatives of the Israeli embassy since the period covered in the Cabinet Office's most recent ministerial gifts, hospitality, travel and meetings data release.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","27635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453700","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-25","<p>I confirmed in a statement on 19 February 2016 that I had authorised the request. Permission was granted once I was satisfied with the legality of the operation.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","27841","2016-02-25T16:04:58.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453700/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453700/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453700/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-22","USA: RAF Lakenheath","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment his Department made of the legality of US airstrikes in Libya before authorising use of RAF Lakenheath for airstrikes in Libya on 19 February 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","27840"
