"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453717","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-29","<p>DECC officials and ministers will continue to discuss, with a range of stakeholders, the options for buildings to contribute to reducing carbon and tackling fuel poverty. Our approach is to consider the overall use of energy in buildings, and not energy efficiency or heat in isolation.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-29T14:51:06.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453717/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453717/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453717/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-22","Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, pursuant to the Answer of 1 February 2016 to Question 24408, if she will discuss with the Sustainable Energy Association and other relevant bodies how to achieve the potential for buildings to contribute to the Government's goals on reducing carbon and tackling fuel poverty.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","27692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453718","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-29","<p>A reformed domestic supplier obligation (ECO) from April 2017, which will run for 5 years, will upgrade the energy efficiency of over 200,000 homes per year tackling the root cause of fuel poverty. Our extension of the Warm Home Discount to 2020/21 at current levels of £320m per annum will also help vulnerable households with their energy bills.</p><p>We intend to focus our efforts through ECO and the Warm Home Discount more effectively on the fuel poor, and will be consulting on our future approach in the spring.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-29T14:48:02.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453718/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453718/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453718/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453718/answer/previousversion/47307","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453718/answer/previousversion/47307",,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-22","Fuel Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what steps her Department is taking to tackle fuel poverty in the UK.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","27764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453719","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-02-25","<p>Such matters fall primarily to the Non-Departmental Public Body Seafish, which is funded by an industry levy. Seafish has developed a ‘Risk Assessment for Sourcing Seafood’ (RASS), an online seafood sourcing tool, to help retailers assess the potential reputational risks of sourcing particular types of seafood. The primary objective is to support commercial seafood buyers by presenting up-to-date information on a comprehensive range of fisheries whose products are in the UK supply-chain, covering four components: stock, management, bycatch, and habitat. This year, RASS will be expanded through the addition of seafood social responsibility factors including crew welfare, human rights and slavery.</p><p>Seafish has also developed, and recently launched at the Houses of Parliament, the Responsible Fishing Scheme (RFS). The RFS is a voluntary vessel-based programme certifying high standards of crew welfare and responsible catching practices on fishing vessels. It is the only programme certifying crew welfare and responsible catching practices on vessels, and complements other fishery-based sustainability certifications. Such assurances are being increasingly sought by the UK market.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-02-25T16:19:23.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453719/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453719/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453719/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-22","Fish Products: Supermarkets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the Government is doing to encourage supermarkets to act responsibly when sourcing and purchasing fish products.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","27737"
